Name: Modern Science Ontology
Description: Urban planning is a technical and political process concerned with the development and design of land use and the built environment, including air, water, and the infrastructure passing into and out of urban areas, such as transportation, communications, and distribution networks

Name: Data Privacy Vocabulary
Description: A data subject that is a citizen of a jurisdiction
Useful_classes: Citizen (classe elle?même), peut être utilisé pour modéliser « habitants/citoyens » dans ton domaine lié aux acteurs du territoire

Name: DBpedia Ontology
Useful_classes: dbo:Person, dbo:Country  relation entre un individu et sa citoyenneté nationale

Name: Schema.org
Description: An organization such as a school, NGO, corporation, club, etc.

Name: Schema.org
Description: The geographic coordinates of a place or event.

Name: domOS Common Ontology
Description: A building represents a structure that provides shelter for its occupants or contents and stands in one place. The building is also used to provide a basic element within the spatial structure hierarchy for the components of a building project (together with site, storey, and space). The basement floor of a building is floor number 0.

Name: ISA Programme Location Core Vocabulary
Description: An "address representation" as conceptually defined by the INSPIRE Address Representation data type. The locn:addressId property may be used to link this locn:Address to other representations.

Name: BBC Core Concepts Ontology
Description: The class of people in the BBC. Subclasses of this can be all types of people such as politicians, athletes, historic figures, contributors in programmes, etc.
Association describes a relationship between two instances of dsd:Concept. There are three dsd:Association subclasses for aggregation, inheritance, and reference associations.
